<refnamediv><refname>immedian3</refname><refpurpose>Apply median filtering to a 3-D volume.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = immedian3(volume)
out = immedian3(volume, window)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist>
<varlistentry><term>volume</term><listitem><para>Numeric 3-D scalar volume.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>window</term><listitem><para>Three positive window dimensions <literal>[rows columns slices]</literal>. Default is <literal>[3 3 3]</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>out</term><listitem><para>Double filtered volume.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para>Replaces each voxel with the median of its bounded 3-D neighborhood using a native C++ implementation. It is suited to sparse impulse noise.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[
volume = zeros(41, 41, 17);
volume(13:29, 13:29, 6:12) = 1;
noisy = volume;
noisy(8, 10, 4) = 5;
noisy(20, 20, 9) = -4;
filtered = immedian3(noisy, [3 3 3]);
imshow3d(filtered, "orthoslice");
]]></programlisting></refsection>
